jobs.title: Web Application Developer (GIS)
jobs.description:
Why It's a Great Opportunity:
As an experienced, creative web application developer specializing in GIS (Geographic Information Systems) applications, with proven technical skills and a consultative mindset, you will focus on implementing complex technical solutions, providing GIS programming expertise, designing system integrations, and helping to set future directions in a changing GIS technology world.

You will be eligible for remote work in accordance with Pierce County and IT remote work policies. Additional onsite work may be required in certain situations and candidates must live within a commuting distance to meet these requirements.

Why It's a Great Department:
Pierce County is a national IT leader in delivering public services through innovation. Our diverse technology solutions are all supported by a robust hybrid infrastructure of on-premises and cloud-based solutions and a secure network.

Spatial Services is a team of fifteen staff within the IT Division supporting countywide GIS at the enterprise level. This includes building and maintaining GIS applications and integrations, managing a spatial database of over 1400 datasets for the county, and providing advanced training and support for approximately 1000 GIS users. We host 600+ GIS web services and support a diverse set of business needs with location-based technology including GPS and drones. We collaborate and partner with GIS professionals and users in the County departments and many regional organizations to understand and meet their needs. We also provide the public with applications and GIS data to assist them with their business needs.

We focus on maintaining a good work life balance and support a continuous learning mindset for employee development. You can directly see the impact of your work through our GIS services that provide data and interactive applications to the public, the provision of GIS services to our regional partners, and supporting County employees in their everyday business processes that help make Pierce County a great place to live, work and play.

How to be Successful in the Role:
Bring your software development skills, your knowledge of the unique aspects of spatial data systems, and a desire for continuous learning to an organization that is a recognized leader in the field. In a rapidly changing IT environment, we need someone who is strong technically as well as adaptable, professional, and a life-long learner who is responsive to customer needs. Collaborative teamwork, creative problem solving and troubleshooting, anticipating needs, and confidence in addition to your technical skills will help you be successful.

Your Future in this Role:
The IT Division has access to numerous training opportunities, which include peer, industry, vendor, and official Pierce County training as well as access to established procedures, standards, practices, and system documentation. Our training program is designed to help you develop as both a professional in your role as a GIS web developer and as a Pierce County employee. Your work will directly impact your community and offers a great foundation for future positions within the IT Division and Pierce County.

Core responsibilities:
• GIS web application development and system integration/implementation.
• Application management including design, development, implementation and maintenance, documentation and use of code repositories, creation and maintenance of procedural documentation, training for user department staff and user support as needed.
• Program, maintain, enhance, integrate and support GIS business systems/programs.
• Successfully troubleshoot system and application issues and identify creative solutions to answer needs.
• Assist senior GIS staff on large scale or complex projects.

Current Projects:
• New web application development and upgrades that utilize ESRI’s JavaScript API 4.x, TypeScript, React framework and ESRI’s Experience Builder developer edition technology. There are a wide variety of applications in this category in the areas of land services, emergency management, commercial investment, community equity, utilities, surface water management, etc.
• Maintenance and feature enhancements of existing web applications using Web App Builder, JavaScript, HTML, CSS.
• Constant improvement in code deployment and code management processes, security, and documentation.
A classification job description with a more detailed list of essential functions and knowledge, skills, and abilities can be found at GIS Programmer-Engineer 1 and GIS Programmer-Engineer 2.
GISPE1 $34.35 – $49.32 per hour, non-exempt
• Bachelor’s Degree in Science, Technology, Engineering, Geography or related field AND
• Two or more years of Information Technology/GIS experience
• Additional education or experience may substitute for the recruiting requirements
GISPE2 $80,381 – $116,420 annually, exempt
• Bachelor’s Degree in Science, Technology, Engineering, Geography or related field AND
• Four or more years of Information Technology/GIS experience
• Additional education or experience may substitute for the recruiting requirements
Preferred Qualifications:
• Demonstrated experience and knowledge with the Esri platform.
• Application development experience in the following programming technologies:
• JavaScript API 3.x/4.x, Esri WebAppBuilder developer edition (TypeScript and Esri Experience Builder experience would be an asset)
• Esri ArcGIS Pro based ArcPy library (ArcMap based ArcPy experience will be considered).
• Esri ArcGIS Pro .Net SDK (ArcMap based ArcObjects experience will be considered. Experience with ArcGIS Pro SDK based development is desirable).

Special Requirements:
• Positions in specific program areas may require program-related experience, education, and/or training
• A valid Washington State Driver's License may be required when travel is required of the position
• As a condition of employment, the applicant will need to authorize and complete a background check. Information received from the background check is reviewed case-by-case and will not necessarily remove an applicant from consideration
To be considered for this opportunity please
• Complete and submit an online Pierce County Employment Application by selecting "APPLY" above or go to: www.piercecountywa.org/jobs.
• Upload a current resume demonstrating your qualifications and skills as described in this job announcement
• If you do not have internet access, you may visit your local public library or any WorkSource location and use their computers.
• Individuals needing accommodation in the application, testing process or need this job announcement in an alternative format may call Human Resources at (253) 798-7480, at least two days prior to the need.
This is a competitive selection process. Your application form will be reviewed and evaluated for the quality and quantity of education/experience in the areas listed. Applicants whose qualifications most closely correspond to the County's needs will be eligible for further consideration. Notification of application status normally occurs 4 to 6 weeks after the closing date. Short notice may be given to applicants to participate in further selection processes which may include written, oral and performance examinations, and final interviews.

At Pierce County, diversity, equity, and inclusion means commitment, not a single step. We strive to foster an inclusive environment that supports equitable access to opportunities throughout your career. We want to recruit, develop, and maintain a talented workforce from various backgrounds, cultures, lifestyles, and perspectives, committed to our vision. Employees of the County have local, direct, and visible impact in our diverse community. Will you join us in keeping Pierce County a great place to live, work, and raise a family?

jobs.title: University Web Developer and User Experience Designer
jobs.description:
Job Summary

The University Web Developer and User Experience Designer reports
directly to the Assistant Director of Web Development, UX, and
Content, and receives additional general direction from the Digital
Director of Marketing and Communications, and art direction from
the Senior Director of Creative Strategy and Branding. This
position is a key member of the Digital Marketing and
Communications (Digital) team responsible for the visual and
functional design of the sjsu.edu website(s). The incumbent
continually develops and designs the look and feel driving the San
José State University web presence; integrates user experience
design best practices; and contributes to content strategy. The
position is responsible for the web programing, design and
maintenance methods, production and visual development of the
sjsu.edu home page, web templates, web components, tools and custom
integrations, news pages and sites, top-level pages within the site
map, all pages and sites managed by University Marketing and
Communications (UMC) and the Office of the President, and
enterprise-wide web and digital media. The incumbent also provides
consultation and general web design and content assistance to other
university departments as appropriate.

Key Responsibilities
• Support the core SJSU website(s) with continually updated
graphics, multimedia and visual user-interface improvements.
• Support the visual development of communications outlets
including the SJSU Newsroom, Washington Square Magazine Digital
Issues, and various campaign and other fundraising web
properties.
• Design web interfaces and collaborate with UMC and other
stakeholders on the development of interface pattern
libraries.
• Integrate design patterns to university websites, campaign
websites, blogs, emails, and other digital platforms.
• Following the general digital marketing direction from the
Director of Digital Marketing and Communications and art direction
provided by the Senior Director of Creative Strategy, create a
consistent visual design for the SJSU.edu website.
• Apply universal design principles ensuring accessibility of
digital content and applications.
• Align content strategy initiatives with user experience project
plans.
• Contribute to web project planning, strategy and
documentation.
• Collaborate with internal and external developers on web
components/templates /integrations requiring more advanced
development, scripting and programming.
• Collaborate with technical and creative contributors to
coordinate changes to SJSU’s interface design patterns and
templates.
• Provide web graphics and general web content support to SJSU
divisions and departments.
• Stay current new user-centered design trends and UX
strategies.
• Create web and interface concept sketches, flows, wireframes,
mockups, and prototypes to support the design process.
• Conduct user research using formal and informal methods,
interpret user needs, gather requirements by consulting
stakeholders, analyze web analytics, and assess current
interfaces.

Knowledge, Skills & Abilities
• Extensive knowledge of interface, photo and graphic design
software, including Photoshop, Illustrator, After Effects, Figma,
Adobe Xd, Sketch and iMovie Premiere Pro
• Knowledge of TextMate, TextWrangler, Sublime Text, Dreamweaver,
MS Visual Studio Code or other code-editing tools
• Knowledge of content management systems, WordPress, Modern
Campus and Drupal templates, email marketing tools, and video
editing software
• Thorough knowledge of universal design and web accessibility
standards
• Ability to work with CSS Frameworks and maintain responsive web
design libraries
• Familiarity with the scripting language JavaScript and
JavaScript libraries
• Extensive knowledge of HTML, JavaScript, React, XML, XSL, SML,
CSS, CMS systems, or similar blogging platforms. Google Analytics.
Tableau, Looker Studio, Lucidchart and Adobe Creative Suite
• Strong graphic design skills and artistic ability to translate
communication needs into design
• Familiarity with and interest in emerging technologies,
including HTML5, CSS, Python, Artificial Intelligence (AI),
etc.
• Comprehensive knowledge of visual design principles as applied
to online media
• Ability to understand university level curriculum concepts and
convey them graphically
• Knowledge of experience designing and crafting user experiences
that are responsive
• Ability to sketch or prototype interactions and design concepts
with Sketch, Figma, Adobe Xd or similar UI design tools, as well as
Invision, Keynote, Principle, or similar prototyping tool
• Knowledge of user research techniques, usability testing,
surveys, card sorting, interviews, contextual inquiries, cognitive
task analysis, and heuristic evaluations
• Knowledge of combining key research findings to create
personas, use cases, and user journeys
• Knowledge of web analytic software, Google Analytics, Looker
Studio, and Search Engine Optimization (SEO) Practices

Required Qualifications
• Bachelor’s degree in computer science, information systems,
educational technology, communications, or related fields, or
similar certified coursework in applicable fields of study
• Three years of experience supporting information systems and
technology

Preferred Qualifications
• Experience with interface, photo and graphic design software,
including Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign and Premiere Pro
• Experience wire framing and prototyping interactions and design
concepts with Sketch, Figma, Adobe Xd or similar UI design tools,
as well as Invision, Keynote, or similar prototyping tool
• Experience with HTML/CSS, Modern Campus, Drupal and WordPress
CMS

jobs.title: Front-End Software Engineer (Web Developer)
jobs.description:
Front-End Software Engineer (Hybrid or Remote)

RouteSmart Technologies, a leader in vehicle route optimization software technology, is seeking a front-end software engineer for their development team in Melville, NY. This role will be responsible for designing, coding, and supporting multiple websites that must feature both user-friendly design and clear navigation, from layout to function.

The typical base pay range for this position at the start of employment is expected to be between $100,000-$110,000 per year. RouteSmart Technologies, Inc. has different base pay ranges for different work locations within the US and base pay will vary based on experience.

This position is hybrid or remote; however, we are currently seeking only candidates who are domiciled in the following states: Maryland; New York; Pennsylvania; Arizona; California; Colorado; Florida; Idaho; Illinois; Indiana; Minnesota; New Jersey; North Carolina; Oregon; South Carolina; Washington

Essential Duties & Responsibilities
• Create site layout/user interface by using standard HTML/CSS practices
• Write well designed, testable, and efficient code by using best software development practices
• Demonstrate the ability to identify and fix errors in code
• Integrate data from various back-end services and databases and consult other web designers to match visual design intent
• Strong understanding of UI, cross-browser compatibility, general web functions and ECMA Script standards
• Deep expertise and hands on experience creating Web Applications using one or more JavaScript frameworks, such as ReactJS and Material UI
• Understanding of web application security, session management, and code development best practices
• Deep functional knowledge or hands on experience with making calls to Web Services
• Working knowledge of GIS and similar mapping services extremely useful
Education & Experience
• Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, Business Technology, or a related field
• 3+ years minimum experience as a UX designer and/or web developer/front-end software developer preferred
• Experience in planning and delivering software platforms used across multiple products and organizational units

RouteSmart offers its employees numerous opportunities for professional development. Our goal is to provide our employees the chance to learn and grow as the company grows. We recognize that our employees are our most valuable asset. The work they do is key to our ability to provide high quality service to our clients. We also recognize that our employees are unique individuals with their own lifestyle and interests. RouteSmart Technologies pays a significant share of the cost of benefits for our employees. We believe our investment makes good business sense by helping to create a positive and productive work environment. Among the benefits we offer are:
• Medical/Dental/Vision/STD & LTD Plans
• Employer paid Life Insurance Plan
• Employee Training & Development
• 401(k) Retirement Savings Plan w/ Employer Match
• Vacation/Sick/Holiday Leave
• Tuition Reimbursement
